---
<!-- ── SKILLS vs AGENTS vs WORKFLOWS ─────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="border-y border-border bg-surface py-32 max-md:py-20" id="skills-agents-workflows">
  <div class="layout-wrap">
    <div class="fi mb-12 max-w-3xl opacity-0 translate-y-[18px] transition-[opacity,transform] duration-[650ms] ease-out [&.in]:translate-y-0 [&.in]:opacity-100">
      <div class="mb-3.5 text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-text-kicker before:text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)] before:content-['//_']">Who runs what</div>
      <h2 class="mb-5 font-display text-[clamp(30px,3.5vw,50px)] font-bold leading-[1.02] tracking-[-0.06em]">
        Skills, agents,<br /><em class="not-italic text-accent">&amp; workflows.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-[1.75] text-text-dim">
        Your hub stores several kinds of <strong class="font-semibold text-text">markdown</strong>, each with a different job.
        <strong class="font-semibold text-text">Skills</strong> teach the assistant <em>how</em> to approach a class of tasks.
        <strong class="font-semibold text-text">Agents</strong> are separate worker definitions for focused passes (reviews, exploration).
        <strong class="font-semibold text-text">Workflows</strong> are checklists and procedures—often for you to follow end-to-end, with the AI helping step-by-step when you drive the chat through them.
        <strong class="font-semibold text-text">Rules</strong> (above) stay broad guardrails across conversations.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xs leading-[1.75] text-text-dim">
        In your hub after <code class="text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)]">chain init</code>: <code class="text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)]">skills/&lt;slug&gt;/SKILL.md</code>,
        <code class="text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)]">agents/*.md</code>, <code class="text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)]">workflows/*.md</code>, and
        <code class="text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)]">rules/*.md</code> under <code class="text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)]">CHAIN_HOME</code>.
        Repository CI lives under <code class="text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)]">.github/workflows/</code> in a project repo—that is <strong class="text-text">not</strong> the same as hub workflow docs.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-0.5 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article
        class="fi border border-border bg-surface-2 p-7 opacity-0 translate-y-[18px] transition-[opacity,transform,border-color] delay-75 duration-[650ms] ease-out hover:border-[rgba(139,124,255,0.26)] [&.in]:translate-y-0 [&.in]:opacity-100"
      >
        <h3 class="mb-2 font-display text-[13px] font-semibold tracking-wide text-accent">Skills</h3>
        <p class="mb-3 text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-text-faint">Who runs it</p>
        <p class="mb-5 text-xs leading-[1.65] text-text-dim">The assistant in your chat (or an agent that loads the skill).</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-text-faint">What it is</p>
        <p class="text-xs leading-[1.65] text-text-dim">Playbooks: when to use them, steps, output shapes, optional references.</p>
      </article>
      <article
        class="fi border border-border bg-surface-2 p-7 opacity-0 translate-y-[18px] transition-[opacity,transform,border-color] delay-150 duration-[650ms] ease-out hover:border-[rgba(139,124,255,0.26)] [&.in]:translate-y-0 [&.in]:opacity-100"
      >
        <h3 class="mb-2 font-display text-[13px] font-semibold tracking-wide text-accent">Agents</h3>
        <p class="mb-3 text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-text-faint">Who runs it</p>
        <p class="mb-5 text-xs leading-[1.65] text-text-dim">A dedicated subagent session with its own brief—scoped tasks without bloating the main thread.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-text-faint">What it is</p>
        <p class="text-xs leading-[1.65] text-text-dim">A role file (frontmatter + instructions). <code class="text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)]">chain setup</code> can link these into Cursor and Claude Code agent folders.</p>
      </article>
      <article
        class="fi border border-border bg-surface-2 p-7 opacity-0 translate-y-[18px] transition-[opacity,transform,border-color] delay-200 duration-[650ms] ease-out hover:border-[rgba(139,124,255,0.26)] [&.in]:translate-y-0 [&.in]:opacity-100"
      >
        <h3 class="mb-2 font-display text-[13px] font-semibold tracking-wide text-accent">Workflows</h3>
        <p class="mb-3 text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-text-faint">Who runs it</p>
        <p class="mb-5 text-xs leading-[1.65] text-text-dim">Usually you or your team following the doc; the AI can execute pieces when you walk through it together.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-text-faint">What it is</p>
        <p class="text-xs leading-[1.65] text-text-dim">Procedure markdown: prerequisites, ordered steps, checkpoints, verification lists.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div
      class="fi mt-10 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface-2 p-6 opacity-0 translate-y-[18px] transition-[opacity,transform] delay-300 duration-[650ms] ease-out [&.in]:translate-y-0 [&.in]:opacity-100"
    >
      <table class="w-full min-w-[480px] border-collapse text-left text-xs leading-[1.65] text-text-dim">
        <caption class="sr-only">Comparison of skills, agents, and hub workflows</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-border text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-text-faint">
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-left" scope="col">Artifact</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-left" scope="col">Primary executor</th>
            <th class="py-3 font-medium text-left" scope="col">Typical use</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-border align-top">
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-text" scope="row">Skill</th>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Assistant in your chat</td>
            <td class="py-3">Consistent method for a class of tasks (testing, commits, reviews…)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border align-top">
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-text" scope="row">Agent</th>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Subagent / side session</td>
            <td class="py-3">Focused pass (e.g. deep code review) with its own context window</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="align-top">
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-text" scope="row">Workflow</th>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Human-led procedure (AI assists)</td>
            <td class="py-3">Onboarding, audits, release checklists—steps you can tick off</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
